Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil a full #kettle{}.

While it boils, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces.

Pour the @boiled water{600%ml} into a #measuring jug{}. Add the @wild mushroom paste{22%g}, then stir well to combine - this is your mushroom stock.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the onion and @sliced mushrooms{120%g} to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the @risotto rice{175%g} to the pan. Stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in your mushroom stock. Bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}).

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Roasted Garlic and Portobello Mushrooms ==

While the risotto bakes, peel and grate a third of the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Remove the stems from the @portobello mushrooms{2} and pop them onto a #baking tray{}, cut-side up. Add the grated garlic, drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Rub the oil and garlic all over.

Pop the remaining @garlic clove{2}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of oil and scrunch to enclose it.

Roast the mushrooms and garlic parcel on the top shelf until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}.

== Assembly ==

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in the @butter{20%g}, roasted garlic, @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) and @truffle zest{1%sachet}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Transfer your cooked portobellos to a #board{} and slice into strips.

Spoon your mushroom risotto into #bowls{} and top with the sliced portobello mushrooms.

Drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish.

Enjoy!